'''Brevibacterium iodinum''' is a [[Gram-positive]] [[soil]] [[bacterium]]. It can often be found among the normal [[skin flora|cutaneous flora]] of healthy people, particularly in humid environments, and is only very rarely involved in [[opportunistic infection]]s. It is also suspected to be a cause of [[foot odor]].<ref>{{cite web|last=S.|first=Antoniou|title=Brevibacterium iodinum Peritonitis Associated with Acute Urticaria in a CAPD Patient|url=http://www.pdiconnect.com/cgi/reprint/17/6/614.pdf|publisher=www.pdiconnect.com|accessdate=31 March 2011}}</ref>
{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2011}}

