{{pp-move-indef}} '''Dirty Sanchez''' is a purported [[Human sexual activity|sex act]] where [[feces]] are purposely smeared onto a partner's upper lip. Sex-advice columnist [[Dan Savage]] says the act is completely fictional.<ref>{{cite web|title=Do the Santorum|url=http://www.thestranger.com/seattle/SavageLove?oid=14422|last=Savage|first=Dan|date=2003-05-29}}</ref> [[Brian Bouldrey]] in ''Dirty Words: A Literary Encyclopedia of Sex'' says the act is an urban legend.<ref>{{cite book|title=Dirty Words: A Literary Encyclopedia of Sex|publisher=Bloomsbury Publishing|year=2008|isbn=1-59691-474-2}}</ref> The ''[[New Partridge Dictionary of Slang and Unconventional English]]'' says, "This appears to have been contrived with the intention to provoke shock rather than actually as a practice, although, no doubt, some have or will experiment."<ref name="Partridge">Partridge, Eric; Dalzell, Tom; Victor, Terry (2006). ''The new Partridge dictionary of slang and unconventional English.'' Taylor & Francis, 9780415259378</ref>
== Etymology == Columnist [[Gustavo Arellano]] of ''[[¡Ask a Mexican!]]'' contends the term evokes the stereotypical mustache of a Mexican.<ref>{{cite book|title=Ask a Mexican|first=Gustavo|last=Arellano|pages=67|year=2007|isbn=1-4165-4002-4}}</ref> The term for the sex act entered British gay [[Cant (language)|cant]] [[Polari]] in the 1960s.<ref name="Baker">{{cite book|title=Fantabulosa: A Dictionary of Polari and Gay Slang|last=Baker|first=Paul|year=2004|publisher=Continuum International Publishing Group|pages=109|isbn=0-8264-7343-1}}</ref>
== In the media == American heavy metal band [[Steel Panther]] mentioned Dirty Sanchez in their song titled "The Shocker" from their album ''[[Feel the Steel]]'' (2009). Another band, [[Sleazy RoXxX]], recorded a song called "Dirty Sanchez" as the opener for their album ''[[Topless Suicide]]''' (2016).{{fact|date=June 2018}}
In the ''[[South Park]]'' episode "[[Proper Condom Use]]" (2001), the Filthy Sanchez is noted as a sexual act, among several other allusive terms for sexual acts. "Hot Karl" was also mentioned.{{fact|date=June 2018}}
A 2004 advertisement for [[Unilever]]'s Seedy Sanchez [[Pot Noodle]] featured a [[Mariachi]] band singing a song filled with [[double entendre]]s about their noodles and the sex act.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZuxbnWuP6wM|title=Pot Noodle Ad – Seedy Also seen in scary movie 4 Sanchez}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Pot Noodle continues innuendo in new TV ad|url=http://www.brandrepublic.com/Campaign/News/204400/Pot-Noodle-continues-innuendo-new-TV-ad/|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120630110053/http://www.brandrepublic.com/Campaign/News/204400/Pot-Noodle-continues-innuendo-new-TV-ad/|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2012-06-30|publisher=Brand Republic|date=2004-03-05}}</ref>
In the movie ''[[Dodgeball:A True Underdog Story]]'' (2004), after their victory over the girl scout troop, they{{who|date=November 2018}} meet White Goodman and his team in a bar called "The Dirty Sanchez". The side of the building shows a woman with a moustache holding a beer.{{fact|date=June 2018}}
It was mentioned in the film ''[[The 40-Year-Old Virgin]]'' (2005) along with [[rusty trombone]] by Mooj after learning Andy is a virgin.{{fact|date=June 2018}}
In 2006, [[Dustin Diamond]] directed and released his own sex tape ''Screeched – Saved by the smell'' (2006), which was marketed as depicting Diamond performing the sex act.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.nydailynews.com/2006-09-27/gossip/18343532_1_tape-alice-cooper-glam|title=Porn Star's Name May Ring A 'Bell'|publisher=New York Daily News|date=2006-09-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thehollywoodgossip.com/2006/10/screech-sex-tape-guest-stars-revealed/|title=Screech Sex Tape "Guest Stars" Revealed|publisher=The Hollywood Gossip|date=2006-10-04}}</ref> The film's marketer [[David Hans Schmidt]] appeared on the ''[[Howard Stern Show]]'' in October 2006, and Stern confirmed the act was performed in the film.<ref name="Stern2006">{{cite web|url=http://www.howardstern.com/rundown.hs?d=1160539200|title=The Howard Stern Show for October 11, 2006|date=2006-10-11}}</ref>
The US [[Federal Communications Commission]] (FCC) has ruled that the term is actionably indecent. [[WXYT-FM|WKRK-FM]] in [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]], has twice been fined for using the term on air.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fcc.gov/eb/Orders/2003/FCC-03-71A1.html|title=NOTICE OF APPARENT LIABILITY FOR FORFEITURE |publisher=Federal Communications Commission|date=March 28, 2003}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fcc.gov/eb/Orders/2004/FCC-04-49A1.html|title=NOTICE OF APPARENT LIABILITY FOR FORFEITURE |publisher=Federal Communications Commission|date=March 8, 2004}}</ref> However, Rosenblat notes that the act was discussed and the term used frequently by [[Howard Stern]].<ref>{{cite journal|last=Rosenblat|first=Geoffrey|title=Stern Penalties: How the Federal Communications Commission look to crackdown &#91;sic&#93; on indecent broadcasting|pages=167|issue=13|year=2006|journal=Villanova Sports & Entertainment Law Journal LIES}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last=Rosenblat | first=Geoffrey | date=2006 | title=Stern Penalties: How the Federal Communications Commission and Congress Look to Crackdown &#91;sic&#93; on Indecent Broadcasting | url=https://digitalcommons.law.villanova.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1103&context=mslj | website=DigitalCommons.Law.Villanova.edu | publisher=Jeffrey S. Moorad Sports Law Journal | access-date=2018-01-06}}</ref>
The television show ''[[Family Guy]]'' referenced it in an episode but made up the variation 'muddy Ramirez' due to network censoring.<ref>{{Cite web | author=Morgan Jeffery | date=November 2, 2011 | title='Family Guy' Alex Borstein interview: 'I'd love to make a movie' | url=http://www.digitalspy.com/tv/interviews/a347654/family-guy-alex-borstein-interview-id-love-to-make-a-movie.html | website=DigitalSpy.com | access-date=2017-03-24}}</ref>
In DC Comics' ''[[Suicide Squad]]'' #22, the term was replaced with a made-up term, 'sloppy aardvark', in order to avoid editorial objections to the script.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bleedingcool.com/2013/12/22/when-a-dirty-sanchez-gets-replaced-by-a-sloppy-aardvark/|title=When Harley Quinn Replaces A Dirty Sanchez With A Sloppy Aardvark |publisher=Bleeding Cool|date=2013-12-22}}</ref>
== In commerce == The Texas-based restaurant chain Torchy's Tacos offers a breakfast taco named the "Dirty Sanchez" on their regular menu. There is no obvious relation between the taco and the purported sex act.<ref>[https://torchystacos.com/menu/ Torchy's Tacos menu]</ref>
